              <tr><td colspan="3">    <table width="600" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
    <tr><td width="200" valign="top"><b>Initiate Symbol of Bertoxxulous</b><br>
MAGIC ITEM LORE ITEM NO DROP <br>
AC: 3<br>
Charges: Unlimited<br>
+1 WIS, +3 MANA<br>
Effect: Disease Cloud<br>
WT: 0.1<br>
Class: CLR<br>
Race: GNM, HUM</td>
    
    <td width="100" align="center" valign="top">
    <b>Item Icon</b><br>
    <img src="itemicons/neck016.jpg"></td>

    <td width="160" valign="top">
    <b>Obtained From (level)</b><br>¤ Quest (10)<br>
</td>
    <td width="140" valign="top">
    <b>Additional Info</b><br>
    Type: Armor, Neck<br>
AC Per Stone: 30<br>
Zone(s): akanon<br>
Date Added: 09/02/00<br>
Last Updated: 09/12/00<br>
<a href="itemsheet.php3?id=2628" target="_blank">Printable Version</a></td></tr>
    </table>
    <br><br>
    <b>Description</b><br>
GETTING STARTED:<br>
Hail Evah Xokez (the evil Cleric guildmistress) in the Necromancer guild. She will ask you if you find the rust and disease in the mines pleasing. Say "I find it pleasing" and she will tell you that you have the potential to become a loyal follower of Bertoxxulous. She will then ask you if you are [willing to learn] the ways of Bertoxxulous. Say "I am willing to learn" and she will give you part 1 of the quest.
<br><br>
PART 1:<br>
Your first task is to infect a pregnant rat in Steamfont with the plague rat disease so that she will pass it on to her bretheren and those she encounters. The "a female rat" is a new mob type in Steamfont, and very grouchy (maybe she's PMSing? hehe). She is about lvl 9 and will attack ANYTHING that comes near her. You WILL need a person that can Charm, and hopefully Track her down, as she is wandering and Steamfont is a very confusing place. Once Charmed, give her the vial. She will disappear, you will get the quest-bell sound, and find an empty vial in your inventory to give back to Evah for Part 2.
<br><br>
PART 2:<br>
Upon returning the vial, Evah will give you a container and instruct you to go collect reagents so that she can mix another batch of plague rat disease. She will want you to gather two Diseased Bone Marrow, one Gnomish Spirits, and one Sprig of Wormwood. First, the Diseased Bone Marrow is a semi-rare drop off of "brittle skeleton"s that roam Steamfont, especially the valley west of the windmills. The Gnomish Spirits, for those of you that don't know, are a beer and can be bought in the bar inside the Zoo building. Lastly, the Sprig of Wormwood is obtained by finding Enixxy Frennor in Steamfont. Follow the aforementioned valley to the west of the windmills that the skeletons hang out in and then hug the wall along your right side coming out of the valley.  You should see Enixxy. She IS a merchant, and DOES sell Wormwood, but not the kind you want. Her stuff is also, by the way, mostly junk. Don't waste your money buying any of it. Ask her "what about wormwood" and she will give you the Sprig of Wormwood. Combine your four items in the box, give it back to Evah and you have completed the quest! Congratulations!!
<br><br>
IMPORTANT NOTE: You MUST do Part 1, as the only way to obtain the container for Part 2 is to turn in the vial from Part 1.
<br><br>
submitted by: Archizek of E'ci / Cyllin of Test<br><br>
<b>Player Comments</b> (total:8, showing:1-5) <a href="JavaScript:popComment('comment.php3?type=item&tid=2628')">add</a><br>
<a href="mailto:weirdoguy@hotmail.com">Cyllin</a> of the Test server on Sep. 12, 2000 at 06:56pm said...<br>
Dangit!  I keep remembering stuff right after I post! 8)

My original reason for sending this in and not keeping it a secret for myself (ehehe!) was to inspire more people to try out evil Gnome/Human Clerics and other odd combinations, in hopes that the servers won't be as saturated with Wood Elf Druids (heaven only knows how many people play those...) and people will be encouraged to take a different path that may not offer the most flashy spells or the coolest-looking race, or the ability to solo best, but instead suits their personality better.



Here's to hoping that I won't think of something else after I hit that darned "Submit" button!<br><br>
<a href="mailto:weirdoguy@hotmail.com">Cyllin</a> of the Test server on Sep. 12, 2000 at 06:52pm said...<br>
D'oh!  One more thing!  This is an incredibly handy spell.  Basically it stops the mob from regaining HP (or at least slows it down) for six full minutes *and* does 5 damage!  Combine this with a no-mana cost and it's a very useful spell.  The biggest downside is that Verant just about tripled the casting time.  I know the regular is 1 second, this one is around 3.  Pretty frustrating.  I mean, it's not like you can chain-nuke someone into submission, it only does 5 damage and by the level that you will probably be able to get it (providing that there isn't some huge Friendly-Newbie-Helping-Druids guild party in Steamfont at the time...) 5 damage will be next to worthless.  ALSO... (man I'm long-winded today 8) I'd say 10 is about the right level, perhaps 8-10.  The brittle skeletons are about the same as regular skellies that also roam the valley, but seem to have more than their fair share of HPs.  Better be good at timing those spells between hits ;)<br><br>
<a href="mailto:weirdoguy@hotmail.com">Cyllin</a> of the Bertoxxulous server on Sep. 12, 2000 at 06:48pm said...<br>
Hey!  I sent in the picture!

Oh well, nothing special.  If you guys are *really* lazy ;) it looks the same as the Order of Thunder from Drosco and the various NPC Pallies.<br><br>
<a href="mailto:weirdoguy@hotmail.com">Cyllin</a> of the Test server on Sep. 08, 2000 at 05:49pm said...<br>
Elleric is right, so far the only *known* deities with symbols are The Tribunal, Bertoxxulous, Innoruuk, and Cazic-Thule.  The Tribunal and Bertoxxulous are so far, to my knowledge, still limited to Initiate while Cazic-Thule is up to at least Disciple and Innoruuk is fully decked out, ending with a very nice Regent Symbol.

Should Verant complete the lines and possibly add new ones, I think I'm not the only person that will be literally jumping with joy.<br><br>
